@startuml Rendex Sequence Diagram

!theme plain
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam sequenceParticipantFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceBoxFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceGroupFontSize 10

participant "Owner\n(MetaMask)" as Owner
participant "Frontend\n(Next.js)" as Frontend
participant "RendexToken\n(Solidity)" as RendexToken
participant "CDIOracle\n(Solidity)" as CDIOracle
participant "Oracle Service\n(AWS Lambda)" as Lambda
participant "BCB API" as BCB

== Daily CDI Update (00:00 UTC — AWS EventBridge) ==

Lambda -> BCB : GET /dados/serie/bcdata.sgs.12/dados/ultimos/1
BCB --> Lambda : CDI daily rate (e.g. 0.0641%)
note right of Lambda
  Converts daily % to basis points:
  Math.round(0.0641 * 100) = 6 bp
  No 120% multiplier here — that
  is applied inside rebase()
end note
Lambda -> CDIOracle : updateCDI(6)
CDIOracle --> Lambda : Transaction Receipt
CDIOracle -> CDIOracle : emit CDIUpdated(6, timestamp)

== Manual Rebase (Owner via Admin Panel) ==

Owner -> Frontend : Click "Trigger Rebase"
Frontend -> RendexToken : rebase()
RendexToken -> CDIOracle : getCDI()
CDIOracle --> RendexToken : 6 (daily basis points)
note right of RendexToken
  rebaseRate = 6 * 120 / 100 = 7 bp
  newSharesPerToken = sharesPerToken
    * (1 + 7 / 10000)
  All balances increase automatically
  via balanceOf override
end note
RendexToken -> RendexToken : update sharesPerToken
RendexToken -> RendexToken : update lastRebaseTime
RendexToken -> RendexToken : increment rebaseCount
RendexToken --> Frontend : emit RebaseExecuted(count, cdiRate, rebaseRate, newSharesPerToken, timestamp)
Frontend --> Owner : Transaction confirmed + Etherscan link

== User Balance Check ==

Owner -> Frontend : Connect Wallet (MetaMask)
Frontend --> Owner : Wallet connected
Frontend -> RendexToken : balanceOf(ownerAddress)
note right of RendexToken
  returns shares * sharesPerToken / 1e18
  Grows automatically after each rebase
  without any transfer or mint
end note
RendexToken --> Frontend : balance (in RDX = R$)
Frontend -> CDIOracle : getCDI()
CDIOracle --> Frontend : current daily CDI (basis points)
Frontend -> RendexToken : sharesPerToken()
RendexToken --> Frontend : current unit price accumulator
Frontend --> Owner : Display position (R$), unit price (R$), CDI rate

@enduml
